{"TopicId":137603,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Kopernicus Help","CreatedByName":"WillThe84th","CreatedById":154644,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-21T15:38:38Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"WillThe84th","CreatedById":154644,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-21T15:38:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to remove a planet in Kopernicus? Because I need to remove Laythe for a mod I\u0027m making.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy solution for right now is to just make Laythe orbit itself, but I was wondering if there is another way.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-21T15:39:59Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2016 03:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by WillThe84th\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MrHappyFace","CreatedById":76365,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-21T20:20:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust remove the Laythe node from the Kopernicus config using ModuleManager:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\nKopernicus:AFTER[Kopernicus]\n{\n\t//removes Laythe node\n\t!Body[Laythe]\n\t{\n\t}\n}\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-21T20:20:25Z\u0022 title=\u002204/21/2016 08:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MrHappyFace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WillThe84th","CreatedById":154644,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-21T22:40:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, the other way just seemed kinda cheaty.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}